mention.text: her whom earth adores , -- The Lady of the dove-drawn car
stars that shine ; The comet and the penny show , All curious things , above , below
The little hero of the hunch
him whose optic glass supplies The crowd with astronomic eyes
A siren singing by the Seine
many a ringing silver dime , For him whose optic glass supplies The crowd with astronomic eyes
The last new-comer of the file
each his place must fairly earn
O blessed , beauteous evening star , Well
he who looks upon the stars Through the red atmosphere of Mars

a rayless spot , Blank as a careless scribbler 's blot , Stripped of thy robe of silvery flame , -- The stolen robe that Night restores When Day has shut his golden doors , -- I see thee , yet I know thee not ; And canst
a rayless spot , Blank as a careless scribbler 's blot , Stripped of thy robe of silvery flame
Stripped of thy robe of silvery flame
a world like ours , Flung from the orb that whirled our own A molten pebble from its zone
The fire-waves of the blazing orb
hast thou cities , domes , and towers , And life
new suns , new systems gleam ; The voice no earth-born echo hears
O guardian of the starry gate , What coin shall pay this debt of mine ?
too small the fee That bids thee turn the potent key The Tuscan 's hand
